    <div class="body">
        <p>In times like these where mobile internet access is growing rapidly it would be awesome to easy check if user-agent is mobile.
I thought it would be best placed in Zend_Controller_Request_Http?</p>

<p><code>
protected static $_mobileUserAgentNeedles = array(
    'iPhone',
    'Android',
    'webOs',
    'BlackBerry',
    'iPod',
    'Windows Mobile',
    'Windows Phone',
    'Opera Mini',
    'Opera Mobi',
    );</code></p>

<p>public function getIsMobileUserAgent()
{
    for($i = 0; $i &lt; count(self::$needles); $i++)
    {
        return strpos($user_agent, $needles[$i]) &gt; 0;
    }</p>

